<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[The world this week]]></title><link/> https://www.economist.com/the-world-this-week/ <atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/economist/the-world-this-week" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[The world this week - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RS集线器</generator><webmaster>i@diygod.me (DIYgod)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 9 月 3 日，星期日 13:06:40 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[This week’s covers]]></title><description><![CDATA[<p data-component="paragraph" class="css-1hno3qs e190yofl0"><span data-caps="initial">有</span><small>几周</small>，包括这几周，我们发布了不止一张封面。在世界大部分地区，我们都在考虑人工智能将如何影响 2024 年的选举。<br><br>政治本应是说服，但它却一直被宣传所困扰。过去，虚假信息一直是人类制造的。现在，生成人工智能的进步——其模型可以吐出复杂的文章并根据文本提示创建逼真的图像——使合成宣传成为可能。人们担心，2024 年，正当总人口约 40 亿的国家（包括美国、英国、印度、印度尼西亚、墨西哥和台湾）准备投票时，虚假信息宣传活动可能会加剧。他们的公民应该有多担心？ </p><div class="css-0 eitqf4z0"><style data-emotion="css qts40t">.css-qts40t img{display:block;}.css-qts40t .edweubf2{margin-top:0.25rem;}</style><figure class="css-qts40t e1197rjj0"><img alt="" loading="lazy" width="1280" height="1684" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color:transparent" sizes="(min-width: 960px) 834px, 95vw" srcset="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=360,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_US.jpg 360w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=384,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_US.jpg 384w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=480,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_US.jpg 480w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=600,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_US.jpg 600w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=834,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_US.jpg 834w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=960,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_US.jpg 960w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1096,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_US.jpg 1096w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1280,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_US.jpg 1280w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_US.jpg 1424w" src="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_US.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></figure></div><p data-component="paragraph" class="css-1hno3qs e190yofl0"><b>领导人：</b> <a href="https://www.economist.com/leaders/2023/08/31/how-artificial-intelligence-will-affect-the-elections-of-2024">人工智能将如何影响 2024 年的选举<br></a><b>美国：</b> <a href="https://www.economist.com/united-states/2023/08/31/ai-will-change-american-elections-but-not-in-the-obvious-way">人工智能将改变美国选举，但不会以明显的方式改变</a></p><style data-emotion="css 11rnjw">.css-11rnjw{margin:0;border-width:0;border-top:1px solid var(--ds-color-london-85);}</style><hr class="css-11rnjw e10jdj00"><p data-component="paragraph" class="css-1hno3qs e190yofl0">在欧洲、中东和非洲，我们思考偏执的民族主义是如何导致腐败的。<br><br>世界各地愤世嫉俗的领导人正在使用夸张和谎言来赢得和滥用权力。弗拉基米尔·普京声称乌克兰是<small>北约的</small>傀儡，其纳粹集团威胁着俄罗斯；印度执政党警告称，穆斯林正在发动一场“爱情圣战”来引诱印度教少女。偏执民族主义的宣扬者显然伤害了他们言论的目标，但他们的真正目的是欺骗自己的追随者。通过煽动民族主义热情，自私的领导人可以更容易地赢得权力，一旦上任，他们可以通过大声疾呼所谓的敌人来转移公众对他们滥用职权的注意力，否则这些敌人本来会遏制他们。 </p><div class="css-0 eitqf4z0"><figure class="css-qts40t e1197rjj0"><img alt="" loading="lazy" width="1280" height="1684" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color:transparent" sizes="(min-width: 960px) 834px, 95vw" srcset="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=360,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_EU.jpg 360w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=384,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_EU.jpg 384w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=480,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_EU.jpg 480w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=600,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_EU.jpg 600w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=834,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_EU.jpg 834w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=960,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_EU.jpg 960w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1096,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_EU.jpg 1096w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1280,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_EU.jpg 1280w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_EU.jpg 1424w" src="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_DE_EU.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></figure></div><p data-component="paragraph" class="css-1hno3qs e190yofl0"><b>领导人：</b><a href="https://www.economist.com/leaders/2023/08/31/how-paranoid-nationalism-corrupts">偏执的民族主义如何腐败<br></a><b>简报：</b><a href="https://www.economist.com/briefing/2023/08/31/why-paranoid-nationalism-fosters-corruption">愤世嫉俗的领导人正在煽动民族主义以赢得和滥用权力<br></a><b>榕树：</b><a href="https://www.economist.com/asia/2023/08/31/south-east-asian-democracy-is-declining">为何东南亚民主正在衰落</a></p><hr class="css-11rnjw e10jdj00"><p data-component="paragraph" class="css-1hno3qs e190yofl0"><i>仅限订阅者：要了解我们如何设计每周的封面，请订阅我们的每周<a href="https://www.economist.com/newsletters/cover-story">封面故事时事通讯</a>。</i></p>空]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 31 Aug 2023 14:52:39 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> /内容/edf412f846b2042rk2ahfji32871376p</guid><link/> https://www.economist.com/the-world-this-week/2023/08/31/this-weeks-covers </item><item><title><![CDATA[Politics]]></title><description><![CDATA[<section class="css-1ugvd2u e18wk22u0"><style data-emotion="css qts40t">.css-qts40t img{display:block;}.css-qts40t .edweubf2